The paper deals with data structures and complexity bounds for Boolean matrix-vector multiplication, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper presents a new cell probe data structure and complements it with lower bounds, which are typical topics in the area of data structures and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with complexity bounds, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also mentions succinct data structures, which could place it in cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
